    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: BENDIX 2150 - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>GENERAL</title>
            <para>The compressor is driven by the vehicle engine and is operating continuously while the engine is
                running. Actual compression of air is controlled by the compressor unloading mechanism and the governor.
                The governor is generally mounted on the compressor and maintains the brake system air pressure between
                a preset maximum and minimum pressure level.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
